{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-12928/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-12928"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:29:28"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["low key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["man in bed looks up at woman in wedding dress"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-12928","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-12928"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/canvas/1/f7c836ea-c71d-4317-bc7e-2c8ffce06e58","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:23:44.309Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds says that he can’t hear his mother’s voice, despite calling out to her and seeing her in his dreams. In the film, the characters so often communicate without words, so this is a troubling dynamic for him.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:564.1558441558432,70.90909090909079,766.7532467532467,912.4675324675326"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/canvas/1/f5f3b569-f295-4f3b-9351-dab46b258e54","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T18:25:43.841Z","creator":"lucia","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Although his mother remains silent, this piece in the score, “Never Cursed,” features string flourishes that suggest someone calling out to listeners. It’s as if the score—embodying Mrs. Woodcock’s voice—is what awakens Reynolds. In this way, image and sound work in tandem to convey the film’s themes of communing with the dead and familial connection.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-12928/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:28.831168831167915,49.870129870129674,383.37662337662334,207.27272727272737"}}}]}]}]}